The case against former Wits SRC leader and Fees Must Fall activist Mcebo Dlamini has seen yet another postponement following his lawyer being admitted in a hospital.Dlamini made a brief appearance at the Johannesburg Magistrate&#8217;s Court on Tuesday after he told the court that his lawyer had to seek medical attention and that he was not going to be able to make it in court.He faces charges of possession of a dangerous weapon, theft, assault with grievous bodily harm, malicious damage to property and public violence.Dlamini was arrested in October 2016 at the Witwatersrand University s Junction Residence Complex and was released on R2,000 bail in November in the Palm Ridge High Court.Mcebo Dlamini speaks out on charges against himHe will be back in court again on, September 7, to make final arrangements for an attorney.-TNA Reporter &nbsp;